[2] USA: children, women cases
Date: Mon 25 Jul 2022
Source: CIDRAP [edited]
https://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2022/07/who-director-declares-monkeypox-public-health-emergency


Late last week, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) said the nation now had 2 confirmed cases of monkeypox in children, following similar announcements in the Netherlands and Spain.

The detections likely reflect household transmission, the agency said, and are unrelated. One is a toddler from California, and the other is a baby who isn't a US resident but was tested while traveling through Washington, DC.

The CDC also said at least 8 cases in the US have been in women.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[It seems reasonable that the cases in children likely were in close contact with infected men since men are the overwhelmingly greatest component of the population that is infected. - Mod.TY]

