[3] Canada (Yukon territory)
Date: Sat 23 Jul 2022
Source: Outbreak News Today [abridged, edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/canada-yukon-reports-1st-monkeypox-case-28821/


The 1st monkeypox case has been reported in Yukon, according to Yukon's Chief Medical Officer of Health, Dr Sudit Ranade.

"On Thursday, 21 Jul 2022, the 1st case of monkeypox was confirmed in the territory.

"Yukon Communicable Disease Control (YCDC) is conducting a thorough investigation into this case and the individual is in isolation. In this case, we understand that the exposure to monkeypox occurred outside of the territory.

As of 22 Jul [2022], the Public Health Agency of Canada (PHAC) has reported 681 cases of monkeypox in Canada.

